  "handBuiltBaseline": 467,
  "_bar": [
    "DWFUI adoption is measured, not asserted. The old bar was `assert.match(source, /\\bDWFUI\\b/)` --",
    "a file merely had to CONTAIN THE STRING, so a module that mentioned DWFUI in a comment and then",
    "hand-rolled 17 buttons passed as `migrated`. Two modules did exactly that.",
    "",
    "builderCall = a call to one of DWFUI's *Html builders, through any receiver (several modules",
    "alias DWFUI to a local, e.g. `const D = _anUI()`). `esc`/`require` do NOT count -- they are",
    "utilities, not UI.",
    "handBuilt  = <button>/<input>/<select> elements the module still writes itself, i.e. controls",
    "             DWFUI owns builders for. This is the debt, and it may only shrink.",
    "",
    "migrated    = builderCalls >= 1 AND handBuilt == 0",
    "partial     = builderCalls >= 1, with `handBuilt` stating exactly what is still hand-built",
    "queued      = builderCalls == 0 (the module does not use DWFUI, whatever its comments say)",
    "specialized = exempt, and must say why in `reason`"
  ]
}